3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates TRX/USDT funding rates hourly based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments when negative. The exchange's institutional-grade matching engine on Sui enables precise execution with minimal slippage. Settlement occurs automatically every hour with instant finality thanks to Sui's high-throughput consensus mechanism."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TRX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TRX/USDT represents significant funding opportunities due to TRON's large DeFi ecosystem and staking yields that often create directional bias. The pair's substantial trading volume across multiple venues provides consistent arbitrage potential. Bluefin's position as Sui's leading perpetual DEX offers unique access to this major altcoin pair with professional execution quality."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"TRX Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TRX/USDT funding rates on Bluefin typically correlate with TRON network activity and staking rewards distribution cycles. During high DeFi activity periods, positive funding rates often emerge as traders take leveraged long positions anticipating increased TRX utility. The hourly funding frequency allows for more granular arbitrage compared to 8-hour cycles on other platforms. Historical data shows funding rates ranging from -0.05% to +0.15% during volatile periods, with neutral periods clustering around ±0.01%."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently arise between Bluefin and centralized exchanges due to the DEX's unique position in the Sui ecosystem. The 0.02% maker fee structure allows profitable arbitrage even on smaller rate differentials. Traders can exploit funding rate discrepancies by maintaining opposing positions across venues while earning the spread. Bluefin's fast settlement on Sui enables rapid position adjustments as funding dynamics shift throughout each hourly cycle."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Trading TRX perpetuals on Bluefin involves Sui network risks, including potential validator issues or network congestion during high activity periods. The DEX's relatively lower volume compared to tier-1 centralized exchanges may result in wider spreads during volatile market conditions. Cross-chain bridge risks exist when moving USDT collateral to and from Sui. Additionally, the early-stage Sui ecosystem could face unforeseen technical challenges that impact trading operations and funding rate calculations."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are TRX/USDT funding rates updated on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin calculates and settles TRX/USDT funding rates every hour, providing more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. The exact funding payment occurs at the top of each hour with automatic settlement."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for TRX/USDT perpetuals on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for TRX/USDT perpetual trades. These competitive rates allow for profitable funding rate arbitrage strategies even with smaller rate differentials between exchanges."},{"question":"Can I trade TRX perpetuals on Bluefin without KYC?","answer":"As a decentralized exchange on Sui, Bluefin allows TRX/USDT perpetual trading without KYC requirements. You only need to connect a compatible Sui wallet to begin trading, though geographic restrictions may apply."},{"question":"What is the maximum leverage for TRX/USDT on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin typically offers up to 20x leverage for TRX/USDT perpetual futures, though the exact leverage may vary based on market conditions and risk management parameters. Lower leverage is recommended for funding rate arbitrage strategies to minimize liquidation risk."}]}]
